  "text": "RESEARCH ARTICLE Disease Models & Mechanisms (2016 ) 9, 401-412 doi:10.1242 experimental groups (Fig. 3A) . Protein expression was, however, still significantly reduced in the hypothalamus of recuperated animals at 3 months (P<0.05; Fig. 3B ,C). Given that perturbations of ARC 5-HT 2C R function increases appetite and body mass [CITATION_1] , these results reveal a potential mechanism through which rapid postnatal growth is achieved in recuperated rats, which could also contribute to increased susceptibility to diet-induced obesity in these animals.",
